<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb9665845-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8" identifier="/us/usc/t18/s2338"><num value="2338">§ 2338.</num><heading> Exclusive Federal jurisdiction</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The district courts of the United States shall have exclusive jurisdiction over an action brought under this chapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idb9665846-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/102/572/tX/s1003/a/4">Pub. L. 102–572, title X, § 1003(a)(4)</ref>, <date date="1992-10-29">Oct. 29, 1992</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/106/4524">106 Stat. 4524</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idb9665847-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idb9665848-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="idb9665849-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section applicable to any pending case or any cause of action arising on or after 4 years before <date date="1992-10-29">Oct. 29, 1992</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/102/572/s1003/c">section 1003(c) of Pub. L. 102–572</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t18/s2331">section 2331 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
